    "Interpreting and Analysing Hartree-Fock Results Observables in Hartree-FockAt the end of the HF iteration procedure, the one-body density matrix P can be examined to understand its properties.",
    "Consider a one-body observable Ô =k,sτ τ ′ ab O τ a,τ ′ b (k, s)ĉ † τ,a (k, s)ĉ τ ′,b (k, s) that preserves momentum and spin.",
    "The expectation value of this operator in the HF state is⟨O⟩ P = 1 N 1 N 2 Tr(P O) = 1 N 1 N 2 k∈mBZ τ τ ′ sab P τ ′ b,τ a (k, s)O τ a,τ ′ b (k, s),(51)where the normalization is chosen so ⟨O⟩ P is defined per moiré unit cell.",
    "We can use O τ a,τ ′ b (k, s) = [τ z] τ τ ′ δIVC = 1 N 1 N 2 k∈mBZ sab |P K ′ b,Ka (k, s)| 2,(52)which probes the valley off-diagonal part of the HF projector.",
    "More generally, given a symmetry of the original Hamiltonian represented by Û, we can characterize the degree of symmetry-breaking in the HF state viaS Û = 1 N 1 N 2 ∥P -P Û ∥ 2."
